Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly elevated triglycerides, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Liver function, electrolytes, glucose, and protein levels are normal. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and consideration of lipid management.
